## Joining a Zoom meeting with a telephone

You can [join a Zoom meeting by phone](https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/201362663-Joining-a-Meeting-by-Phone) if you cannot access it from your computer.  
  

1. The meeting host should provide you with a local number to call (such as an 0800 or 020 number) to use through the meeting invitation. Check the [full list of Zoom dial-in numbers](https://zoom.us/zoomconference).

2. When joining by phone, youâ€™ll be prompted to enter the Meeting ID. This is a 9, 10, or 11 digit ID provided to you by the host, followed by #. If you cannot find the Meeting ID, contact the meeting organiser. You might also be prompted for a passcode which you should enter. If you do not know the passcode, you should ask the meeting organiser for it.

## Set up a test call on Zoom

You can join a [test Zoom meeting](http://zoom.us/test) to familiarise yourself with Zoom and [test your computer audio and video](https://support.zoom.us/hc/en-us/articles/201362283-Testing-computer-or-device-audio). While in a Zoom meeting, you can select your Microphone and Speaker by selecting the up arrow between the Mute and Start Video options.
